Perhaps the approval process is procedurally intricate, but I believe I
recall seeing that only something on the order of 1 out of 900 federal
wiretap court order requests in a recent year was declined.  This indicates
[choose one or more, according to degree of paranoia]:

  1.  Nearly infallible investigators / prosecutors
  2.  Rigorous administrative review before the request gets to a judge
  3.  Rubber stamp judges

